tra or a deity ETC. This need &lt;br&gt;a still body and then a stil=\r\nl mind. First the mind will become calm. Then eventually the mind will\n bec=\r\nome quite. In a normal human mind there is a constant running commentary go=\r\ning on. That needs to be stopped eventually. When that is done, without or =\r\nwithout a mantra, various kinds of interesting experiences come to the seek=\r\ner. But the problem with this method is that, its gains are often limited t=\r\no only the time frame when you are stilling and concentrating. Once you go =\r\nback to teh world, your gains are either lost or frittered away. It takes a=\r\n really long time to get such a one-off experience in focused concentration=\r\n which is powerful enough to change your surface personality even during ot=\r\nher times. For most seekers, such a thing never happens. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Contemplat=\r\nion is when you keep your focus on a mantra or a deity even with engaging i=\r\nn all kinds of activities. This is a process of knowing by becoming. If you=\r\n keep contemplating constantly for days on end on one specific things, you =\r\nwill often gain some knowlege/understanding about it by way of\n association=\r\n. This is a very useful sadhana. Unlike concentration, this can be and is m=\r\nent to be done even while doing all other things. &lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;When you do both,=\r\n that is focused concentration while keeping the body still, and contemplat=\r\nion of Divine at all points even when engaged in other activities, then a d=\r\nual effect accrues in your system which has a greater chance of changing yo=\r\nur surface daily personality. For all sadhana eventually must do just that.=\r\n&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;**realization, the English word, is super vague. In spiritualit=\r\ny, if one does an objective reckoning of scriptures, paths, sadhanas, and e=\r\nxperiences of various legendary sadhakas one will see that there are vast m=\r\nultidimensional number and nature of great spiritual realizations. And they=\r\n are not similar at all. It is a complex and interesting study in itself. T=\r\nhe proverbial reality is One, but it is so complex that few, even among gre=\r\nats, have ever had a complete realization of all aspects\n of the One. &lt;br&gt;&lt;=\r\nbr&gt;-Regards&lt;br&gt;&nbsp;Rajarshi&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;i&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;div class=3D=\r\n&quot;MsoNormal&quot;&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class=3D&quot;Apple-style-span&quot; style=3D&quot;font-size:16px;&quot;&gt;&lt;=\r\nb&gt;&lt;span class=3D&quot;Apple-style-span&quot; style=3D&quot;color:rgb(153, 153, 153);&quot;&gt;&lt;/sp=\r\nan&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span class=3D&quot;yui_3_2_0_2_134243527249950&quot; style=3D&quot;font=\r\n-family:times new roman, new york, times, serif;&quot;&gt;awaktam wyaktimApannam ma=\r\nnyantE mAmabuddhayah |&lt;/span&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;span class=3D&quot;yui_3_2_0_2_134243506227=\r\n946 yui_3_2_0_2_134243527249952 yui_3_7_2_27_1351102131325_71&quot; style=3D&quot;FON=\r\nT-SIZE:10pt;COLOR:navy;FONT-FAMILY:Verdana;&quot;&gt;&lt;font color=3D&quot;#000000&quot; face=\r\n=3D&quot;Times New Roman&quot;&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;div&gt; param bhAwamajAnanto mamAwyayamanuttamam ||=\r\n[7:24]&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;d=\r\niv style=3D&quot;font-family: Courier New, courier, monaco, monospace, sans-seri=\r\nf; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt; &lt;div style=3D&quot;font-family: times new roman, new york,=\r\n times, serif; font-size: 12pt;&quot;&gt; &lt;div dir=3D&quot;ltr&quot;&gt; &lt;font face=3D&quot;Arial&quot; si=\r\nze=3D&quot;2&quot;&gt;\n &lt;hr size=3D&quot;1&quot;&gt;  &lt;b&gt;&lt;span style=3D&quot;font-weight:bold;&quot;&gt;From:&lt;/spa=\r\nn&gt;&lt;/b&gt; vishal vijaywargiya &lt;vishal_vijaywargiya@...&gt;&lt;br&gt; &lt;b&gt;&lt;sp=\r\nan style=3D&quot;font-weight: bold;&quot